<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="58" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 23700/14.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Bryan</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-12"><hi rend="italic">April 12,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Hale instructs Minister Bryan to cooperate with Minister Beaupré at
                            The Hague, from whom he may obtain particulars, to secure permission
                            from Government of Belgium for transit of agent and extradited
                            criminal.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>